    <section class="section">
        <h2>Vision</h2>
        <p>Parachute is an open knowledge layer for humans and AI to think and remember together. The shape: a personal knowledge graph organized around <strong>notes, tags, and links</strong>, accessible to any AI via MCP&mdash;the open standard for connecting AI to tools.</p>
        <p>We ship two pieces that share one schema and one storage layer.</p>
        <p><strong>Parachute Daily</strong> is the way you put thoughts in. A voice-first journaling and capture app for phone, web, and pendant, with three tabs: Reader, Capture, and Vault. Local on-device transcription, fully offline-capable, syncs to your vault when connected. <a href="/vision/">Read the full vision &rarr;</a></p>
        <p><strong>Parachute Vault</strong> is where they live, and how every AI you use reads them. A self-hosted knowledge graph exposed over MCP, with 20+ tools, semantic search, wikilink auto-linking, and Obsidian import/export. One command sets it up. Each vault is its own SQLite database.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <h2>Progress This Semester</h2>
        <p>Since the semester started in mid-January, 200+ pull requests merged across the repository have transformed Parachute from an early prototype into a near-launch platform. Here's the arc:</p>

        <h3>January: Foundation</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Built a multi-agent daily system with reflection agents and a content-scout that processes journal entries</li>
            <li>Added API key authentication for multi-device access</li>
            <li>Shipped local voice transcription using Sherpa-ONNX with Parakeet models&mdash;works fully offline on macOS and Android</li>
            <li>Built a CI/CD pipeline with code signing, notarization, and automated DMG builds for macOS distribution</li>
            <li>Designed the product architecture and wrote the <a href="/archive/prd-modular-architecture.html">Modular Architecture PRD</a>&mdash;the design document that shaped the rebuild</li>
            <li>Published this documentation site at openparachute.io</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>February: The Big Build</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Completely rewrote the server as <strong>Parachute Computer</strong>&mdash;12,800+ lines of new code in under two weeks</li>
            <li>Built the module system: brain, chat, and daily as independent modules with SHA-256 hash verification</li>
            <li>Implemented three trust tiers (full / restricted / sandboxed) with Docker container isolation for untrusted sessions</li>
            <li>Built Telegram and Discord bot connectors with a per-user pairing and approval flow</li>
            <li>Created the <code>parachute</code> CLI for install, daemon management, config, diagnostics, module management, and updates</li>
            <li>Added workspaces&mdash;named capability scopes that control which tools, MCPs, and models are available per session</li>
            <li>Built the unified Flutter app with an adaptive multi-panel layout (mobile / tablet / desktop)</li>
            <li>Decomposed large monolithic files into focused services&mdash;chat_service.dart went from 2,059 lines to 9 focused files</li>
            <li>Built the event-driven hooks system for extending behavior at every lifecycle point</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>March: Graph as Core Infrastructure</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Dissolved Brain as a standalone module&mdash;the graph became core infrastructure connecting everything</li>
            <li>Memory feed UI, MCP Cypher tools, graph-native entity system</li>
            <li>Unified projects and conversation schema into a single coherent graph</li>
            <li>Hardened Daily: durable audio staging, offline sync fixes, graph-native agent definitions (Callers &amp; Cards)</li>
            <li>UI polish across the app&mdash;approaching launch readiness</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Late March / Early April: The Vault Pivot</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Recognized the right shape: an open knowledge layer accessible to any AI via MCP, not a closed agent platform tied to one orchestrator</li>
            <li>Spun out <strong>Parachute Vault</strong> as a focused standalone repo (Bun + TypeScript + bun:sqlite)&mdash;notes, tags, links, and 20+ MCP tools as the core primitives</li>
            <li>One-command install: <code>vault init</code> creates a vault, starts a launchd/systemd daemon on port 1940, and registers it with Claude Code's MCP automatically</li>
            <li>Multi-vault support: one daemon hosts many isolated SQLite vaults, each with its own API key and per-vault MCP description</li>
            <li>Wikilink auto-linking, semantic search via sqlite-vec, bidirectional Obsidian import/export</li>
            <li>Refocused <strong>Parachute Daily</strong> on capture: three-tab UI (Reader / Capture / Vault), offline cache, vault sync</li>
            <li>NVC pitch built and presented&mdash;framed Parachute as "the note-taking system you've been looking for"</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <h2>What Exists Today</h2>

        <h3>Parachute Vault</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Self-hosted knowledge graph with notes, tags, links, attachments &mdash; one SQLite database per vault, multi-vault on one daemon</li>
            <li>20+ MCP tools: get/create/update/delete notes, search, tag/untag, links, graph traversal, find-path, semantic search</li>
            <li>REST API with full CRUD, full-text search (FTS5), and a Whisper-compatible transcription endpoint via parachute-scribe</li>
            <li>Wikilink auto-linking with alias, anchor, and embed support; auto-resolves dangling links when targets appear</li>
            <li>Semantic search via sqlite-vec with pluggable embedding providers (OpenAI, local Ollama)</li>
            <li>Bidirectional Obsidian import/export preserving frontmatter, tags, wikilinks, and paths</li>
            <li><code>parachute vault</code> CLI: init, status, create, list, remove, import, export, config, restart</li>
            <li>Background daemon via launchd (Mac) and systemd (Linux); Docker, Railway, and Fly.io deployment configs</li>
            <li>Per-vault API keys with localhost bypass; remote access via Cloudflare Tunnel</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Parachute Daily</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Flutter app for iOS, Android, and macOS (<code>computer.parachute.daily</code>)</li>
            <li>Three-tab UI: <strong>Reader</strong> (content to process), <strong>Capture</strong> (voice and typed thoughts), <strong>Vault</strong> (search and browse)</li>
            <li>Voice capture with local Sherpa-ONNX transcription&mdash;works fully offline</li>
            <li>Offline-first architecture: SQLite cache + pending-write queue that flushes when reconnected to the vault</li>
            <li>Speaks the Parachute Vault REST API directly; multi-vault aware</li>
            <li>Saved views, tag browser, full-text search</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Parachute Pendant</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>PCB designed and printed in-house; wood front panel prototype</li>
            <li>Hardware pendant for always-on voice capture, feeding directly into a vault</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

