    <section class="section">
        <h2>Revenue Path</h2>
        <p>Parachute Vault is free and open source for self-hosters, always. Revenue comes from making the experience effortless for people who don't want to run a server, and from add-ons that compose on top of the free core. We're not competing with anyone's AI subscription&mdash;we're the $2&ndash;10 add-on that makes whichever AI you already use dramatically better.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Free</strong>&mdash;offline journal and self-hosted vault. No hosting cost on our side.</li>
            <li><strong>$2/mo</strong>&mdash;hosted vault: cloud sync, MCP endpoint, multi-device. Lower COGS than agentic platforms because we're storing structured data, not running inference.</li>
            <li><strong>$5/mo</strong>&mdash;cloud transcription so capture never depends on your laptop being on.</li>
            <li><strong>$10/mo</strong>&mdash;AI reflections and weekly synthesis on top of your vault.</li>
            <li><strong>$100 once</strong>&mdash;the pendant. Always-on voice capture, in development with Marvin Melzer.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Our first 2,000 paid users come from three channels: Learn Vibe Build AI cohorts, the Claude and ChatGPT power-user communities where people are actively looking for better memory tools, and our Boulder co-working space as a local testbed.</p>
    </section>

